{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "For instance, in the nonsensical statement, \"my dad grew volleyballs in his garden,\" the words \"volleyball\" and \"garden\" create a semantic contradiction that goes against commonsense.",
    "Identifying the nonsensical concepts, which essentially serve as the origin of the sentence's departure from commonsense, is beneficial for ensuring the generated explanations clarify the conflict within the statement.",
    "To identify the nonsensical concepts, we employ a transformer-based PLM to compute the perplexity [24] of the statement and analyze the change in perplexity when specific words are masked.",
    "This method allows us to pinpoint the elements that most significantly deviate from commonsense expectations.",
    "Then in the second stage, after identifying the nonsensical concepts, we reconstruct implicit knowledge based on the concepts to assist in generating more accurate explanations."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To identify the nonsensical concepts, we employ a transformer-based PLM to compute the perplexity [24] of the statement and analyze the change in perplexity when specific words are masked."
  ]
